layer.title: Overarching goals
layer.annotation: Goal: Prepare system for installing packages Tool: Alpine Linux. Subtool: Busybox shell Result: successResult
Goal: Obtain, build, and test the latest source distribution of GNU `help2man`. Tool: Alpine Linux. Subtool: Busybox shell Result: successResult
Goal: Dump this shell's history to the terminal and a file at the path "/history" Tool: Alpine Linux. Subtool: Busybox shell Result: successResult

layer.title: Individual commands
layer.annotation: Goal: Prepare Alpine's package manager for installing packages from the core and community libraries. Tool: The `setup-apkrepos` script executed by the shell interpreter included in the BusyBox multi-call binary Mistakes: `ap` is typed at the beginning of the command line before being noticed and erased. Result: successResult
Goal: Download the latest GNU M4 source distribution archive from GNU's servers. Tool: GNU `wget` Result: successResult

Goal: Extract the newly-downloaded GNU M4 source distribution tarball to the current working directory. Tool: The `tar` tool included in the BusyBox multi-call binary Mistake: An superfluous argument starting with `s` is typed after the full command line before being corrected. Result: successResult
Goal: Descend into the newly-extracted directory containing the GNU M4 source distribution. Tool: The `cd` shell builtin included in BusyBox's shell interpreter. Result: successResult

Goal: List all files in the current working directory (the root of the GNU M4 source distribution). Tool: The `ls` tool included in the BusyBox multi-call binary Discovery: There is a script named `bootstrap` included in the `m4` source distribution. Result: successResult

Goal: Bootstrap the GNU M4 source distribution. Tool: The BusyBox shell interpreter running the `bootstrap` script included in the source distribution of GNU M4 Discoveries: GNU `m4` is required to run `bootstrap`. The `bootstrap` script appears to be for GNU M4 developers and packagers. Result: successFailure

Goal: Configure the GNU M4 source distribution for building. Tool: The distribution's included `configure` script ran by BusyBox's shell interpreter. Discovery: A functioning C compiler is necessary to build GNU M4. Result: successFailure
Goal: Install the GNU C Compiler Collection and standard C library development headers. Tool: The `add` subcommand of the `apk` pacage manager included with Alpine Linux. Result: successResult

Goal: Configure the GNU M4 source distribution for building. Tool: The distribution's included `configure` script ran by BusyBox's shell interpreter. Discovery: A functioning C compiler is necessary to build GNU M4. Result: successFailure
Goal: Install GNU Make from Alpine's package repositories. Tool: The `apk` package manager included with Alpine. Result: successResult

Goal: Configure the GNU M4 source distribution for building. Tool: The `configure` script included with the GNU M4 source distribution (running under the BusyBox shell interpreter) Result: successResult
Goal: Build the GNU M4 source distribution. Tool: GNU `make` Result: successResult
Goal: Install the newly-built GNU M4 to the configured `PREFIX`. Tool: GNU `make` running the `install` target in the makefile generated from the GNU M4 source distribution. Result: successResult
Goal: Verify that GNU M4 installed to the expected `PREFIX`. Tool: The `which` tool included with the BusyBox multi-call binary. Result: successResult
Mistake: While typing `m4 --version`, the operator mistypes `mf --` before correcting their mistake. Result: successResult

Goal: Dump the shell's history to a file named `history` in the system's root directory (`/`). Tool: The BusyBox shell interpreter's `history` builtin Mistake: The operator deliberates between redirecting to a file (`>`) or piping to another program (`|`) a couple of times. Result: successResult
